logstrSignificant (Overloaded) Log an important event. If the first character of the string is W, then it will go into the windows log as a warning. If it is a 'E' it would go into the event log as an error. Otherwise it is logged as information. However, the windows Event log is only added to if g_bLogEvents is true.
logstrVerbose (Overloaded) Adds a string to the list of log lines. If log list is already at the maximum, the oldest log line is removed from the list.
